edu.umass.cs.reconfiguration.interfaces

Interface ReconfigurableRequest

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Request
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppRequest, DefaultAppRequest

    public interface ReconfigurableRequest
extends Request
    Author:
    V. Arun

    A reconfigurable request can also be a stop request and comes with an epoch number. The application must be aware of both of these if it uses any coordination protocol other than paxos.
